  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">FLEGT compliance in Ghana: developing the capacity of Loggers without processing mills.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ending the project, forty (40) loggers had benefitted from trainings in ideal felling practices and safety during logging in compliance with FLEGT legality requirements.  The project also produced training manuals and infographics on safety and health for loggers as well as a guide on FLEGT compliance for the Loggers (https://ndfwestafrica.org/flegt-compliance-in-ghana/).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Loggers without processing mills</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project&#x2019;s sought to build the capacity of 40 concession holders without processing mills to comply with private sector obligations under Principles 1, 2, 3 and 4 of Ghana&#x2019;s timber legality definition &#x2013; Source of Timber, Timber Rights Allocation, Timber Harvest Operations and Transportation in Ashanti, Eastern, Central and Western regions of Ghana.</narrative>
  </description>
